Package: admetshiny
Type: Package
Title: Interactive ADMET and Drug-Likeness Analysis of Small Molecules
Version: 1.0.0
Date: 2025-01-01
Authors@R: person("Xavier Clemente", "Garcia Cevallos", email = "xgarcia@unicauca.edu.co", role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-3284-2363"))
Maintainer: Xavier Clemente Garcia Cevallos <xgarcia@unicauca.edu.co>
Description: Provides an interactive 'shiny' application and a toolbox of
    R functions for the management, calculation, filtering, visualization and
    exploratory analysis of molecular descriptors and ADMET (Absorption,
    Distribution, Metabolism, Excretion and Toxicity) properties of small
    molecules. It integrates workflows from SwissADME, ADMETlab 3.0 and
    Deep-PK, computes descriptors locally via the Chemistry Development Kit
    (CDK), and offers drug-likeness filters (Lipinski, Veber, Ghose, Egan,
    Muegge), the BOILED-Egg model, PCA, t-SNE, radar plots and Tanimoto/AGNES
    clustering to support compound prioritization in early-stage drug
    discovery.
